added.title: Terra-ized
added.description: Beast Boy falls for Terra despite clear signs that she is more interested in destroying the Titans.

added.title: Matched
added.description: When a computer dating program matches Beast Boy to Raven, he tries wooing her to disastrous effect.

added.title: Pirates
added.description: When Aqualad and Raven fall for each other, Beast Boy fights this match - with intensity.

added.title: Rocks and Water
added.description: Raven and Beast Boy are shocked to discover that their exes, Terra and Aqualad, are now dating each other.

added.title: The Power of Shrimps
added.description: Aqualad uses shrimps and prime rib to win back Raven.

added.title: That Will Be All
added.description: Steven and the Gems make a daring escape!

added.title: Super Watermelon Island
added.description: Steven finds out what happened to all those sentient watermelons he created.

added.title: Sworn to the Sword
added.description: Connie trains with Pearl to be a swordfighter.

added.title: Onion Trade
added.description: A boy trade between Steven and Onion escalates to epic proportions.

added.title: Lion 2: The Movie
added.description: Steven and Connie try to ride the Lion to the movie theater but Lion has other ideas.

added.title: The Understanding
added.description: Gumball and Darwin find themselves in serious trouble when they agree to everything the new kid in school says. The truth is they can't understand a word that he says. Peter Pepperoni has been home schooled and developed a very odd way of speaking. Due to a series of misunderstandings Gumball and Darwin end up on the run from the law.

added.title: The Uncle
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are desperate to meet Ocho's famous uncle.

added.title: The Upgrade
added.description: Gumball and Darwin see an advert for the latest, cutting-edge Bobert operating system and excitedly talk Bobert into downloading it. At first it seems like a massive improvement, but the many flaws in the new operating system become increasingly apparent.

added.title: The Triangle
added.description: Gumball is jealous when Darwin discovers a hidden musical talent, and he may not be the only one. Darwin joins the school marching band, and his tin-whistle talent lands him the solo. Gumball misses having his friend to goof off with and tries to get rehearsal cancelled. So when Darwin's whistle is sabotaged nobody believes Gumball is innocent. Gumball, meanwhile, sets out to find the true culprit, or there may be no encore.

added.title: The Treasure
added.description: Anais uncovers a secret that she's convinced will lead her to the Watterson's hidden family treasure.

added.title: TKO Rules!
added.description: KO and TKO decide to swap places for the day.

added.title: The K.O. Trap
added.description: KO, Rad, and Enid are caught in an especially devious trap.

added.title: KO's Health Week
added.description: KO spends a week dispensing healthy tips to everyone in the plaza.

added.title: Let's Take a Moment
added.description: Mr. Gar and Carol fight a villain from their past.

added.title: Let's Watch the Pilot
added.description: KO, Rad, and Enid look back at the Lakewood Plaza Turbo pilot.

added.title: Varmints
added.description: Bubblegum teams up with Marceline to face a threat to her homestead's citizens.

added.title: Hello China
added.description: In order to get high school credits, Rigby has to pass a foreign language class taught by Benson in China.

added.title: Gymblonski
added.description: Rigby's high school nemesis returns and threatens to ruin his chances at passing gym class and graduating high school.

added.title: Guys Night 2
added.description: The guys want to give Thomas an epic Guys Night before he goes into hiding forever.

added.title: Happy Birthday Song Contest
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to win a happy birthday song contest.

added.title: Walnuts & Rain
added.description: Finn & Jake stumble into two different holes and meet two different fates.

added.description: Finn and Jake are playing catch when Finn accidentally tosses their throwing disc into a gigantic tree.

added.title: El Poder De Los Camarones
added.description: Aqualad usa camarones y carne de primera calidad para recuperar a Raven.

added.description: Finn's worried that Flame Princess still has evil tendencies in her and wants to shift her alignment to good.

added.title: Guitar of Rock
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to help Benson replace an electric guitar signed by a rock star, or Benson's fired.

added.title: The Little Mer-Tiger
added.description: The origin of Tiger is told as a flashback.  As the legend goes, Tiger used to be a mermaid.  One day the evil ruler of the sea, Bubble Grandpa, demanded a hamburger and picked Tiger to retrieve it.  He used his magic sea powers to give Tiger legs and send her ashore.  But Tiger grew to love the land, and with the help of her new friend, Uncle Grandpa, defeated the evil sea ruler and got to keep her legs.

added.title: Largo
added.description: When a mysterious rain cloud plagues Townsville, Bubbles learns things aren't what they seem.

added.title: Under Wraps

added.title: Total Eclipse of the Kart
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls compete in a race against some of their most vicious villains to win whatever is in the Mayor's mysterious box of mystery.

added.title: Pizza Hero
added.description: It's the end of the school year, and as is tradition at Aberdale Elementary, Papa Marianio is slated to dish out his famous pizza along with a spectacle of song and dance. As the kids wait in excitement, they share memories about times with Papa.

added.title: The Fog
added.description: A new villain arrives in Townsville and gives the old villains an enticing offer.

added.title: Pool's Out for Summer
added.description: The boys go to the Aberdale Community Pool for a day of wet fun! While Jeff slowly wades in the shallow end, getting used to the water, Sumo tries to conquer the diving board, redeeming himself from last summer's bellyflop, and Clarence sneaks past the lifeguards into the hot tub for a boiling surprise…

added.title: Rebel Rebel
added.description: The Professor makes new friends, but they may be the wrong crowd.

added.title: The Oct-Father
added.description: When Princess Morbucks steals Octi, Bubbles' reaction surprises everyone, even her sisters.

added.title: Video Makers
added.description: Finn & Jake have creative differences while making the best home movie ever!

added.title: Plant Daddies
added.description: When Ms. Baker pairs up the kids to act as parents for a sprout, Sumo and Clarence learn all about good parenting. Jeff buys toys instead of fertilizer and Chelsea and Kimby get to know each other.

added.title: Space Emperor

added.title: It Was Them

added.title: Tourist Trap

added.title: Hot Stretch
added.description: Ben and Rook encounter a race of elastic, hot-blooded aliens in Undertown who want to use a stolen nuclear fusion engine to activate a volcano! (Introducing Ester, Seebik & the Kraaho.)

added.title: Many Happy Returns

added.title: Mystery Noise

added.title: Collect This

added.title: Malgax Attacks
